{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-situations-page-tsx","path":"/en/situations/life-events/funerals","result":{"data":{"situation":{"title":"Funerals","meta_description":"Rules and recommendations for funerals.","content":{"processed":"<h2>Rules and recommendations</h2>\n<p>Funerals are allowed <strong>but only 15 people can be present</strong>. The general obligations to wear a mask follow hygienic regulations apply. As part of preventative measures, social distance (even when sitting).</p>\n<p>The wake <strong>cannot be held in a restaurant or any other catering facilities</strong>. The general ban on the presence of the public in restaurants applies. After the ceremony, you can gather in your home. <strong>Please follow the rules related to free movement and hygienic regulations, even when consuming food or drink</strong>.</p>\n<p>Funeral services are allowed to operate, the exemption from the ban on the provision of services applies specifically to funeral service establishments, the performance of embalming and conservation, incineration human remains or human remains and placing human remains in urns.</p>\n<p><strong>From November 23rd 2020 there can be a maximum of 20 people present at the funeral. </strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n"},"path":{"alias":"/situations/life-events/funerals"},"changed":"2020-11-21T08:57:22+00:00","valid_from":null,"langcode":"en","created":"2020-11-05T20:44:24+00:00","links":[],"relationships":{"region":[{"name":"All regions of Czechia"}],"icon":{"code":"account_balance"},"situation_type":{"name":"Life events","path":{"alias":"/situations/life-events"},"relationships":{"icon":{"code":"supervisor_account"}}},"measures":[],"related_situations":[{"title":"Services","path":{"alias":"/situations/shops-and-services/services","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"Retail","path":{"alias":"/situations/shops-and-services/retail","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"Keeping in touch with family","path":{"alias":"/situations/seniors/keeping-touch-family","la